From 6db372ba37acec6383be730fce60cc32c0ec0705 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: picoclaw-fork <fork@picoclaw.dev>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 13:57:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] docs: add quick install one-liner for custom fork

Add a prominent install block at the top of the README with a single
command to clone, apply patches, and build the custom fork. Lists
the active patches and links to PATCHES.md for details.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 README.md | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index a48a53d..fb43889 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -24,6 +24,16 @@
 
 ---
 
+> **Quick Install (Custom Fork by [@paoloanzn](https://github.com/paoloanzn/picoclaw))**
+>
+> ```bash
+> git clone https://github.com/paoloanzn/picoclaw && cd picoclaw && ./scripts/apply-patches.sh && cd vendor/picoclaw && make install
+> ```
+>
+> Includes: SOP framework, relaxed exec guard. See [PATCHES.md](https://github.com/paoloanzn/picoclaw/blob/main/PATCHES.md) for details.
+
+---
+
 > **PicoClaw** is an independent open-source project initiated by [Sipeed](https://sipeed.com), written entirely in **Go** from scratch — not a fork of OpenClaw, NanoBot, or any other project.
 
 **PicoClaw** is an ultra-lightweight personal AI assistant inspired by [NanoBot](https://github.com/HKUDS/nanobot). It was rebuilt from the ground up in **Go** through a "self-bootstrapping" process — the AI Agent itself drove the architecture migration and code optimization.
